commit.message:
Added implementation for Cygwin using /dev/clipboard. Added a static seed for the tests.

This still isn't perfect. Some tests are still failing.

Introduced lazy loading, so that modules aren't loaded immediately after importing pyperclip so the user can call set_clipboard() first.

Changed behavior so that copy() and paste() are set to lazy_load_stub_copy() and lazy_load_stub_paste() until the first time copy(), paste(), determine_clipboard(), or set_clipboard() are called. Originally copy() and paste() were set to None, which is how the user could determine if a clipboard mechanism succeeded or not. This is a backwards-incompatible change.

The is_available() function can determine if a clipboard mechanism was loaded or not.

Renamed the init_osx_cmd_clipboard() function to init_osx_pbcopy_clipboard().

Added a warning for cygwin, since there's no implementation for it yet.

Added a ValueError if set_clipboard() wasn't passed a valid clipboard mechanism.

Changed __all__ to include determine_clipboard() and set_clipboard()

Added more comments and documentation in general.

Renamed text_type constant to STR_OR_UNICODE.
Fixed another mistake where 'posix' was checked for OS X instead of 'mac' due to a mistaken merge.
Merge branch 'hugovk-os.name-posix'
